<subSubSection pageNumber="753" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="753">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="753">Note:</emphasis>
Stace &amp; Jarvis (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="753">Bot. J. Linn. Soc</emphasis>
. 91: 439. 1985) designated 87.37 (LINN) as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
, but they treated the name as if first described in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="753">
<volumeTitle>Centuria I Plantarum</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
(1755: 5), when in fact it first appeared in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="753">
<volumeTitle>Flora Anglica</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
(1754: 10) where it is validated solely by a reference to a work by Ray. Under Art. 7.7, the name must therefore be typified in the context of Ray, and so the material in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeusâ€™">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
herbarium is ineligible.
</paragraph>
